\ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20 
An aranea is an intelligent, shapechanging spider with sorcerous powers. In its natural form, an aranea resembles a big spider, with a humpbacked body a little bigger than a human torso. It has fanged mandibles like a normal sp
ider. Two small arms, each about 2 feet long, lie below the mandibles. Each arm has a hand with four many-jointed fingers and a double-jointed thumb.
\par An aranea weighs about 150 pounds. The hump on its back houses its brain.
\par Araneas speak Common and Sylvan.
\par }{COMBAT
\par }{\fs20 An aranea avoids physical combat and uses its webs and spells when it can. In a battle, it tries to immobilize or distract the most aggressive opponents first. Araneas often subdue opponents for ransom.
\par }{\b\fs20 Poison (Ex):}{\fs20  Injury, Fortitude DC 13, initial damage 1d6 Str, secondary damage 2d6 Str. The save DC is Constitution-based.
\par }{\b\fs20 Spells:}{\fs20  An aranea casts spells as a 3rd-level sorcerer. It prefers illusions and enchantments and avoids fire spells.
\par }{\i\fs20 Typical Sorcerer Spells Known }{\fs20 (6/6; save DC 12 + spell level): 0\emdash  }{\i\fs20 daze, detect magic, ghost sound, light, resistance; }{\fs20 1st\emdash }{\i\fs20 mage armor, silent image, sleep.
\par }{\b\fs20 Web (Ex):}{\fs20  In spider or hybrid form (see below), an aranea can throw a web up to six times per day. This is similar to an attack with a net but has a maximum rang
e of 50 feet, with a range increment of 10 feet, and is effective against targets of up to Large size. The web anchors the target in place, allowing no movement.
\par An entangled creature can escape with a DC 13 Escape Artist check or burst the web with a DC 1
7 Strength check. The check DCs are Constitution-based, and the Strength check DC includes a +4 racial bonus. The web has 6 hit points, hardness 0, and takes double damage from fire.
\par }{\b\fs20 Change Shape (Su):}{\fs20  An aranea\rquote s natural form is that of a Medium monstrous
 spider. It can assume two other forms. The first is a unique Small or Medium humanoid; an aranea in its humanoid form always assumes the same appearance and traits, much as a lycanthrope would. In humanoid form, an aranea cannot use its bite attack, webs
, or poison.
\par The second form is a Medium spider\endash humanoid hybrid. In hybrid form, an aranea looks like a Medium humanoid at first glance, but a DC 18 Spot check reveals the creature\rquote 
s fangs and spinnerets. The aranea retains its bite attack, webs, and poison in this form, and can also wield weapons or wear armor. When in hybrid form, an aranea\rquote s speed is 30 feet (6 squares).
\par An aranea remains in one form until it chooses to assume a new one. A change in form cannot be dispelled, nor does an aranea revert to its natural form when killed. A }{\i\fs20 true seeing }{\fs20 
spell, however, reveals its natural form if it is in humanoid or hybrid form.
\par }{\b\fs20 Skills:}{\fs20  Araneas have a +2 racial bonus on Jump, Listen, and Spot checks. They have a +8 racial bonus on Climb checks and can always choose to take 10 on Climb checks even if rushed or threatened.
\par }{\fs36 
