\par Archons speak Celestial, Infernal, and Draconic, but can speak with almost any creature because of their tongues ability.
\par }{COMBAT
\par }{\fs20 Archons generally prefer to meet a foe head-on if it is prudent to do so, but if outmatched, they do what they can to even the odds (usually by employing hit-and run tactics or standing off and engaging a foe with magic before moving into melee).

\par }{\b\fs20 Archon Traits:}{\fs20  An archon possesses the following traits (unless otherwise noted in a creature\rquote s entry).
\par \emdash Darkvision out to 60 feet and low-light vision.
\par \emdash }{\i\fs20 Aura of Menace (Su): }{\fs20 A righteous aura surrounds archons that fight or get angry. Any hostile creature within a 2
0-foot radius of an archon must succeed on a Will save to resist its effects. The save DC varies with the type of archon, is Charisma-based, and includes a +2 racial bonus. Those who fail take a \endash 
2 penalty on attacks, AC, and saves for 24 hours or until they successfully hit the archon that generated the aura. A creature that has resisted or broken the effect cannot be affected again by the same archon\rquote s aura for 24 hours.
\par \emdash Immunity to electricity and petrification.
\par \emdash  +4 racial bonus on saves against poison.
\par \emdash }{\i\fs20 Magic Circle against Evil (Su): }{\fs20 A magic circle against evil effect always surrounds an archon (caster level equals the archon\rquote s Hit Dice). (The defensive benefits from the circle are not included in an archon\rquote 
s statistics block.)
\par \emdash }{\i\fs20 Teleport (Su): }{\fs20 Archons can use greater teleport at will, as the spell (caster level 14th), except that the creature can transport only itself and up to 50 pounds of objects.
\par \emdash }{\i\fs20 Tongues (Su): }{\fs20 All archons can speak with any creature that has a language, as though using a }{\i\fs20 tongues }{\fs20 spell (caster level 14th). This ability is always active.
